{"session_id":"svc-1777981102049538139","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-05T11:38:26.159145415Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-781a15cf-20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-781a15cf\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eBenchmark: axon backend vs JSONL on 1100-bead archive\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;No performance benchmark exists comparing axon backend vs JSONL backend at realistic archive scale (1100 beads). Without this benchmark, the parent epic (ddx-5d49b14e) cannot evaluate its AC6 gate (\u0026#39;axon parity-or-better than JSONL for ready/blocked/show queue ops\u0026#39;).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/bead/ contains backend_jsonl.go but no axon backend implementation (ddx-95ec5ed5, a dep, must land first).\u0026#xA;- No benchmark file exercises ready/blocked/show operations on a 1100-bead corpus.\u0026#xA;- The missing dep edge (ddx-781a15cf → ddx-95ec5ed5) caused the queue to surface this bead prematurely (dep edge should be added via ).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- After ddx-95ec5ed5 (axon backend) and ddx-bbdd7564 (Backend interface) land:\u0026#xA;  - Add cli/internal/bead/benchmark_backends_test.go (or bead_bench_test.go) with:\u0026#xA;    - BenchmarkReady_JSONL_1100: ready queue ops on 1100-bead JSONL corpus.\u0026#xA;    - BenchmarkReady_Axon_1100: same ops on 1100-bead axon corpus.\u0026#xA;    - BenchmarkBlocked_JSONL_1100 and BenchmarkBlocked_Axon_1100.\u0026#xA;    - BenchmarkShow_JSONL_1100 and BenchmarkShow_Axon_1100.\u0026#xA;  - Generate 1100-bead test corpus (mix of open + closed + archived).\u0026#xA;  - Capture wall-time and allocs. Commit results to .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;run-id\u0026gt;/axon-vs-jsonl-benchmark.md.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- axon backend implementation (ddx-95ec5ed5).\u0026#xA;- Adding a CI gate on benchmark results (gate belongs to a follow-up bead).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. Benchmark file exists at cli/internal/bead/benchmark_backends_test.go covering BenchmarkReady, BenchmarkBlocked, BenchmarkShow for both jsonl and axon on 1100-bead corpus.\u0026#xA;2. Runs via: cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test -bench=. ./internal/bead/... -run=\u0026#39;^$\u0026#39; green.\u0026#xA;3. Results document parity-or-better for axon vs jsonl (wall-time + allocs) committed to .ddx/executions/\u0026lt;run-id\u0026gt;/axon-vs-jsonl-benchmark.md.\u0026#xA;4. Benchmark is reproducible via go test -bench.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/bead/... green (unit tests unaffected).\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2,  area:beads,  area:storage,  kind:perf,  backend-migration, triage:needs-investigation\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-5d49b14e\" base-rev=\"e4c86a2de76c59f7131e2576f6d2d6385582a90d\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead description and AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and conservative project defaults (YAGNI, DOWITYTD, no-docs-unless-asked) in this worktree — write whatever the bead asks for.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"attempt_id":"20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1","base_rev":"e4c86a2de76c59f7131e2576f6d2d6385582a90d","bead_id":"ddx-781a15cf","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260505T113820-ec8a5ea1/prompt.md","session_id":"eb-98abacd4","worker_id":""}}}
